00:08:46.250 --> 00:08:47.800
And instead, I'm going
to put this up.

00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:49.060
And this is supposed
to be science.

00:08:49.060 --> 00:08:51.530
I couldn't find a better
image for science.

00:08:51.530 --> 00:08:53.410
But this is what I would
call science.

00:08:53.410 --> 00:08:55.180
So we've studied things
like why "New York

00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:56.840
Times" articles go viral.

00:08:56.840 --> 00:08:58.790
We've gotten all the articles
released by "The New York

00:08:58.790 --> 00:09:01.690
Times" over a six-month period,
over 7,000 articles,

00:09:01.690 --> 00:09:03.470
to look at why certain articles
make the most emailed

00:09:03.470 --> 00:09:05.000
list and why others don't.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:07.360
We've analyze over 500 products
and brands to look at

00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:09.700
why certain products get more
word of mouth than others.

00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:12.270
We've looked at YouTube videos,
a whole host of

00:09:12.270 --> 00:09:13.960
different types of content.

00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:16.390
And based on these insights
we've seen again and again

00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:17.620
that certain principles
both drive

00:09:17.620 --> 00:09:19.110
people to talk and share.

00:09:19.110 --> 00:09:20.490
Unfortunately, it's not cats.

00:09:20.490 --> 00:09:23.507
But these principles can help
us explain why cats and a

00:09:23.507 --> 00:09:26.590
broad variety of things are
talked about and share.

00:09:26.590 --> 00:09:28.320
And so what I'm going to do
today is share a little bit of

00:09:28.320 --> 00:09:30.060
the insights from the book.

00:09:30.060 --> 00:09:31.880
And the book has a
framework in it.

00:09:31.880 --> 00:09:34.860
And what it is essentially
is a recipe, a recipe for

00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:38.080
engineering content to make
it more viral or talkable.

00:09:38.080 --> 00:09:39.920
And people at this point usually
say well, hold on.

00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:42.130
Can you guarantee that something
will go viral?

00:09:42.130 --> 00:09:43.880
We can't guarantee that
something will go viral.

00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:46.440
I can't guarantee that by
reading this book you will be

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:48.720
