the messenger.

00:11:31.560 --> 00:11:33.790
So how many of you heard the
idea of influentials, or

00:11:33.790 --> 00:11:36.160
opinion leaders, or mavens,
connectors, salesmen, those

00:11:36.160 --> 00:11:37.150
sorts of ideas?

00:11:37.150 --> 00:11:38.860
So that's a really
compelling idea.

00:11:38.860 --> 00:11:41.270
So about a decade ago, Malcolm
Gladwell came out with a

00:11:41.270 --> 00:11:43.570
famous book called "The Tipping
Point," great book,

00:11:43.570 --> 00:11:44.810
extremely well written.

00:11:44.810 --> 00:11:48.670
But about half of what is
in that book is wrong.

00:11:48.670 --> 00:11:49.870
And many in the audience
probably have

00:11:49.870 --> 00:11:50.740
realized that already.

00:11:50.740 --> 00:11:53.040
My job as an academic is to
figure out what's right there

00:11:53.040 --> 00:11:54.110
and what's wrong.

00:11:54.110 --> 00:11:57.160
And we focus so much on special
people, the messenger

00:11:57.160 --> 00:11:59.490
of our ideas, we said if we can
just find those hipsters

00:11:59.490 --> 00:12:01.150
in the East Village
and get them our

00:12:01.150 --> 00:12:02.830
product, well we're done.

00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:03.930
Then it's going to catch on.

00:12:03.930 --> 00:12:06.420
But by focusing so much on the
messenger, we've ignored

00:12:06.420 --> 00:12:08.930
something else that's really,
really important and that is

00:12:08.930 --> 00:12:10.120
the message.

00:12:10.120 --> 00:12:12.080
Lots of people don't have
millions of friends or

00:12:12.080 --> 00:12:13.920
millions of followers, yet
they talk about and share

00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:15.360
things all the time.

00:12:15.360 --> 00:12:17.520
And so we need to understand the
psychology of talking and

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.690
sharing to make people share our
stuff, whether they have

00:12:19.690 --> 00:12:22.510
10 friends or 10,000, whether
they're really persuasive or

00:12:22.510 --> 00:12:24.160
not persuasive at all.

00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:25.690
It's sort of like thinking about
the difference between

00:12:25.690 --> 00:12:26.720
jokes and joke tellers.

00:12:26.720 --> 00:12:28.920
So we probably all have a friend
who's a really good

00:12:28.920 --> 00:12:29.760
joke teller.

00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:32.390
When they tell a joke at the
party, everybody laughs.

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:34.300
But there are certain jokes that
are funny regardless of

00:12:34.300 --> 00:12:35.500
who tells them.

00:12:35.500 --> 00:12:36.480
And that's a difference
between the

00:12:36.480 --> 00:12:37.320
message and the messenger.

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:39.780
How we can create content that
people are going to share

00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:42.390
regardless of who's
doing the sharing.

