Let me go check it out.

00:14:23.350 --> 00:14:26.170
So you walk over, you slide open
the doors, and you walk

00:14:26.170 --> 00:14:27.450
inside this phone booth.

00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:29.340
It's a little cramped,
tight space.

00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:31.440
But you notice on the
wall is a phone.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:33.780
And it's not a recent, sort
of payphone looking thing.

00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:35.300
It's a rotary dial phone.

00:14:35.300 --> 00:14:36.975
Ones you have to stick
your finger in and

00:14:36.975 --> 00:14:38.380
dial around in a circle.

00:14:38.380 --> 00:14:40.380
Just for kicks, hold the
phone to your ear and

00:14:40.380 --> 00:14:42.040
dial the number 2.

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:45.220
And someone will pick up the
other line and they will ask

00:14:45.220 --> 00:14:48.080
you whether you have
a reservation.

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:50.780
Reservation, I'm in a phone
booth inside of a hot dog

00:14:50.780 --> 00:14:51.180
restaurant.

00:14:51.180 --> 00:14:53.180
What would I have a
reservation for?

00:14:53.180 --> 00:14:56.880
But if you're lucky and they
