00:14:59.580 --> 00:15:01.530
Please Don't Tell.

00:15:01.530 --> 00:15:03.550
Now, for those who have of
Please Don't Tell, it's a fun

00:15:03.550 --> 00:15:04.110
experience.

00:15:04.110 --> 00:15:05.710
I've been there a couple
times myself.

00:15:05.710 --> 00:15:06.900
But they have violated a lot of

00:15:06.900 --> 00:15:08.480
traditional laws of marketing.

00:15:08.480 --> 00:15:09.690
There's no sign on the street.

00:15:09.690 --> 00:15:11.620
There's no sign in
the restaurant.

00:15:11.620 --> 00:15:13.890
They have made it really
hard to get into.

00:15:13.890 --> 00:15:15.860
Yet they've never advertised
and if you've ever tried to

00:15:15.860 --> 00:15:17.520
call there, you know it's
really hard to get a

00:15:17.520 --> 00:15:18.660
reservation.

00:15:18.660 --> 00:15:20.540
Phones open at 3:00
PM for that day.

00:15:20.540 --> 00:15:22.400
By 3:30, they're all gone.

00:15:22.400 --> 00:15:24.880
People hit redial again and
again to try to get through.

00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:27.100
Really hard to get through,
so many people calling.

00:15:27.100 --> 00:15:29.150
So what did they do to
make them successful?

00:15:29.150 --> 00:15:31.740
Well if you notice, they did
something really cute.

00:15:31.740 --> 00:15:33.880
They made themselves a secret.

00:15:33.880 --> 00:15:35.720
And if you think about secrets,
someone tells you a

00:15:35.720 --> 00:15:39.415
secret, what's the first thing
you do with that information?

00:15:39.415 --> 00:15:40.720
AUDIENCE: You tell everyone.

00:15:40.720 --> 00:15:41.330
JONAH BERGER: You tell
everyone else.

00:15:41.330 --> 00:15:43.450
They tell you not to tell and
what do you do, you turn

00:15:43.450 --> 00:15:44.920
around and you tell
someone else.

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:47.150
Because the fact that it seems
like a secret makes that

00:15:47.150 --> 00:15:50.210
information seem better and it
makes you look really good by

00:15:50.210 --> 00:15:51.190
sharing it.

00:15:51.190 --> 00:15:53.410
You go to that cool bar, you
tell someone else about it,

00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:54.570
you look like you're
an insider.

00:15:54.570 --> 00:15:56.230
You look like you're
in the know.

00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:58.190
And that's this idea
of social currency.

00:15:58.190 --> 00:16:00.530
Just like the car we drive and
the clothes we wear, the

00:16:00.530 --> 00:16:03.420
things we say affect how
other people see us.

00:16:03.420 --> 00:16:05.950
And so we talk about and share
things that give us status by

00:16:05.950 --> 00:16:07.200
association.

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.680
Things like cool bars, but
also cool information of

00:16:09.680 --> 00:16:14.430
