six key steps, six key

00:29:52.260 --> 00:29:54.620
principles that drive people
to talk and share.

00:29:54.620 --> 00:29:57.500
There's social currency, that
idea of status by association.

00:29:57.500 --> 00:29:59.570
We talk about things that make
us look like insiders.

00:29:59.570 --> 00:30:01.070
That make us look
good or smart,

00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:02.530
rather than bad or dumb.

00:30:02.530 --> 00:30:04.590
Triggers or cues in
the environment.

00:30:04.590 --> 00:30:06.710
Rebecca Black, not rocket
science, but viewed more on

00:30:06.710 --> 00:30:09.210
Friday because that's a trigger
to make it top-of-mind

00:30:09.210 --> 00:30:11.970
and make people more likely to
think about it and share it.

00:30:11.970 --> 00:30:13.560
Emotion, when we
care, we share.

00:30:13.560 --> 00:30:15.840
But some emotions we share
more than others.

00:30:15.840 --> 00:30:16.270
Public.

00:30:16.270 --> 00:30:17.530
Again, that idea of
being publicly

00:30:17.530 --> 00:30:19.310
visible increases imitation.

00:30:19.310 --> 00:30:22.080
Apple did a great job about
making their headphones white.

00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:23.840
Now, you can look at how many
people have white headphones

00:30:23.840 --> 00:30:26.360
and use that as a signal of
quality for whether or not I

00:30:26.360 --> 00:30:27.970
should buy that product.

00:30:27.970 --> 00:30:30.040
Practical value, news
you can use.

00:30:30.040 --> 00:30:33.220
And finally stories building a
Trojan horse or a vessel that

00:30:33.220 --> 00:30:35.160
carries your information.

